# Fluff Date: 2026-02-26 19:50:04
<overview>
<p>The Sovetskii Soyuz-class heavy cruiser is one of the most feared and celebrated warship designs in BattleTech history, an 830,000-ton vessel whose devastating arsenal of Imperator-20 naval autocannons led many SLDF officers to classify it as a battlecruiser rather than a heavy cruiser. Built by Blue Nose Clipperships of Mars -- the premier warship manufacturer of the Star League era -- the Sovetskii Soyuz emerged from General Rebecca Fredasa's New Arms Order of 2735, a massive military modernization program launched after Mother Jocasta Cameron wrested control of the Star League's military budget from the neglectful Lord Jonathan Cameron. Approximately 400 vessels were built, an extraordinary production run that made the Sovetskii Soyuz one of the most numerous heavy cruisers ever constructed. The class pioneered automated ammunition handling through three Nirasaki Hornblower computer systems that replaced 80 crew positions, though the automation was prone to occasional failures that crews grimly called brain seizures. The design's most controversial feature was its deliberately reduced armor of just 743 tons -- a calculated trade-off that freed mass for the formidable weapons suite and adequate maneuverability.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>At 830,000 tons and 803 meters in length, the Sovetskii Soyuz is a massive vessel whose weapons suite justifies the unofficial battlecruiser classification that many officers applied to it. Twelve Imperator-20 Series NAC/20 naval autocannons in four turrets form the primary armament, distributed across broadside and aft quarter arcs to deliver crushing kinetic firepower in sustained engagements. Two Killer Whale capital missile launchers in the nose and two Barracuda launchers across the flanks and aft quarters provide long-range striking power, while Sorenstein-45a NL45 naval lasers and Ceres-N Medium Naval PPCs deliver sustained energy fire across multiple arcs. Three Nirasaki Hornblower computer systems automate the ammunition feed systems, replacing 80 crew positions and freeing considerable space for ordnance storage and the eighteen-fighter hangar. The 40X Templar hull is driven by twin Harlan B8-160 engines through a KF King LX jump drive, with KAT 701 communications and ASTROC 4-b targeting systems coordinating the weapons suite. Bowman JK3 improved ferro-aluminum armor protects the hull at 743 tons -- nearly fifty percent less than the smaller Black Lion II battlecruiser -- reflecting the design's deliberate trade of protection for firepower. The Clan refit added a lithium-fusion battery, a fifth docking collar, and expanded fighter capacity to twenty.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The Sovetskii Soyuz entered service as the backbone of the SLDF's heavy cruiser force, with 400 vessels ensuring a massive presence across every fleet command. The SLS De Ruyter served as flagship of the 57th Escort Squadron, where three Sovetskii Soyuz vessels formed the squadron's core -- a sign of the class's suitability for independent and squadron-level operations. The SLS Kharkov earned lasting fame during the Amaris Crisis when it evacuated Generals Araujo and Kim Hyong Suk from Terra, breaking orbit and burning for the LaGrange jump point under fire to carry the SLDF High Command to safety at Freedom Station. The lead ship SLS Sovetskii Soyuz itself was destroyed during Task Force Leonidas's suicide mission against the Caspar drone network defending Terra -- the vessel was the last to go down, and the task force's sacrifice destroyed 106 drones representing forty percent of those deployed in the Terran system. The majority of the original 400 vessels were consumed during the campaign to liberate Terra, with approximately forty surviving to join Kerensky's Exodus fleet.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Sovetskii Soyuz-class heavy cruiser was born from the political turmoil that gripped the Star League in the early eighteenth century. Under Lord Jonathan Cameron, the SLDF's budget had been diverted to the automated space defense system -- the Caspar drone network -- while the private navies of the Great Houses grew stronger. When Mother Jocasta Cameron assumed most of the First Lord's duties in 2734, General Rebecca Fredasa issued the New Arms Order of 2735, declaring her intention to reassert SLDF superiority with new ships and weapons. Blue Nose Clipperships of Mars, the premier warship manufacturer of the era, answered with the Sovetskii Soyuz.</p><p>Naval architects at Blue Nose envisioned a vessel with fearsome fighting abilities capable of fleet missions or independent actions. The resulting design mounted twelve Imperator-20 NAC/20 naval autocannons in four turrets, complemented by Killer Whale and Barracuda capital missile launchers, Sorenstein-45a naval lasers, and Ceres-N Medium Naval PPCs. Three Nirasaki Hornblower computer systems automated the ammunition feed machinery, replacing 80 crew positions but proving prone to occasional failures the crew called brain seizures. The only way to keep the ship swift while carrying such firepower was to reduce armor to 743 tons -- nearly fifty percent less than the smaller Black Lion II battlecruiser.</p><p>Approximately 400 Sovetskii Soyuz vessels were built, and the class vindicated its unusual design in combat. The SLS Kharkov evacuated the SLDF High Command from Terra during the Amaris Crisis, while the lead ship SLS Sovetskii Soyuz was the last vessel destroyed during Task Force Leonidas's sacrifice against the Caspar drones, the task force destroying 106 drones -- forty percent of those deployed at Terra. About forty vessels survived to join the Exodus.</p><p>The Clan refit added a lithium-fusion battery, fifth docking collar, and expanded fighter capacity, while the unique Dire Wolf variant carried a sixth collar for the Clan Wolf flagship. The Dire Wolf became the most famous warship in Clan history when Tyra Miraborg's kamikaze attack killed ilKhan Leo Showers at Radstadt in 3050. The vessel survived to fight at Terra during the ilClan Trial in 3151 -- over four centuries of continuous service from its commissioning as the SLS Kharkov. Other Clan vessels wrote their own stories: Snow Raven's Storm Crow destroyed twenty-six cities during the Scourging of Galedon before being infected with a bioweapon, while Sea Fox's Talismantia was converted to a CargoShip and fought at Regulus. The Blue Nose Clipperships shipyard on Mars was decommissioned after the First Succession War, never reactivated despite changes in ownership from ComStar to the Word of Blake to the Republic.</p>
</history>

